  "doc_id": "22147",
  "text": "A model in which YAP regulates the coordination of contractile activity is also consistent with the substantial increase in the ROCK-mediated stimulates actomyosin contractility to promote furrow formation during cytokinesis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . A role for YAP in the regulation of contractile activity is further supported by our finding that the hyperdynamic phenotype associated with YAP depletion could be rescued by inhibition of RHO or ROCK. It is feasible that the mislocalized excessive cortical activity during furrow ingression in YAP-depleted cells contributes to improper chromosome distribution during cytokinesis, leading to increased multinucleation, micronuclei, and abnormal chromosome numbers. Together, these data suggest that YAP is a component of the regulatory network that controls contractile activity during mitotic exit.",
